    <fr:title text="Interior Point">Interior Point</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>
If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> is a subset of a <fr:link href="/gtop-0004/" title="Euclidean Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0004/" display-uri="gtop-0004" type="local">Euclidean space</fr:link>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is an <html:strong>interior point</html:strong> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> if there exists an <fr:link href="/gtop-000S/" title="Open Ball" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000S/" display-uri="gtop-000S" type="local">open ball</fr:link> centered at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> which is completely contained in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
