                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000I/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>gtop-000I</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/gtop-000I/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Interior Point">Interior Point</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> is a subset of a <fr:link href="/gtop-0004/" title="Euclidean Space" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-0004/" display-uri="gtop-0004" type="local">Euclidean space</fr:link>, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> is an <html:strong>interior point</html:strong> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> if there exists an <fr:link href="/gtop-000S/" title="Open Ball" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000S/" display-uri="gtop-000S" type="local">open ball</fr:link> centered at <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x]]></fr:tex> which is completely contained in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.
</html:p>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
            <fr:tree show-metadata="false">
              <fr:frontmatter>
                <fr:authors>
                  <fr:author>
                    <fr:link href="/boat/" title="Zihang Zeng" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/boat/" display-uri="boat" type="local">Zihang Zeng</fr:link>
                  </fr:author>
                </fr:authors>
                <fr:date>
                  <fr:year>2026</fr:year>
                  <fr:month>3</fr:month>
                  <fr:day>11</fr:day>
                </fr:date>
                <fr:uri>https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000J/</fr:uri>
                <fr:display-uri>gtop-000J</fr:display-uri>
                <fr:route>/gtop-000J/</fr:route>
                <fr:title text="Interior of a Set">Interior of a Set</fr:title>
                <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
              </fr:frontmatter>
              <fr:mainmatter>
                <html:p>
The <html:strong>interior</html:strong> of a subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> of a topological space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, denoted by <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {int}_X\, S]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {int}\, S]]></fr:tex> or <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S^{\circ }]]></fr:tex>, can be defined in any of the following equivalent ways:
</html:p>
                <html:ol><html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {int}\, S]]></fr:tex> is the largest open subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> contained in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.</html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {int}\, S]]></fr:tex> is the union of all open sets of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> contained in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.</html:li>
<html:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {int}\, S]]></fr:tex> is the set of all <fr:link href="/gtop-000H/" title="Interior" uri="https://boatnotabot.com/gtop-000H/" display-uri="gtop-000H" type="local">interior points</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>.</html:li></html:ol>
              </fr:mainmatter>
            </fr:tree>
          </fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
      </fr:mainmatter>
